review_blob: Dark Amber beer with an off white small and moslty diminishing head. Malty aroma witha a malty initial sweetness and a nice balanced bitter finish. Not bad

Pours red/brown with a frothy white head. Smells strongly of salami/smoked bacon or fish if you will, the taste is malty, slightly bitter. It leaves a real strange bitter aftertaste in your mouth, but I actualy liked it some how...
Clear dark brown colour, almost black. Almost no foam, just some big bubbles floating. Aroma of honey and licorice, heavy roasted malts.
Hoppy, flowery flavor. Clear, light amber colour. Slightly sweetish flovoured. Nothing special.
750 ml bottle. A very good Brown Ale. Not too heavy, but clear taste of chocolate and caramel malt. This is definitely my favorite brown ale!!
Very strong banana aroma. Yeast-dry flavour. Hazy golden body with nice head. Quite nice.
Copper color with a white head. The taste is sweet but kind of watery with notes of malts. Finishes kind of bitter.
Bottle. Beautiful, clear light brown beer - completely missing the head. The beer is close to flat. Marked - almost fat - hoppy aroma. Label is a little boring, but in the average.
Murky brown pour with a short tan head. Chocolate cake and icing sugar aroma. Citrus, coffee, chocolate and toffee resonate throughout. Quite nice.
Very nice bottle and brown color. Definitely not my kind of beer. Its taste is too bitter. I will not be drinking this beer again. Has a taste and smell of Whiskey.
Very nice bottle. Definitely not my kind of beer. Its taste is too bitter, and it shouldnt be called "strong ale". I will not be drinking this beer again. Has a taste and smell of Whiskey.
A nice, fruity pilsner. Yellow with a good but short lived head. A good danish beer!
Dark golden colour with small head. Aroma is sweet and malty, flavor is malty with a sweet touch, slightly hoppy finish.

Bottle, 33cl. Hmmm, what can i say about this beer that hasnt already been said? This is a wonderful beer! All macrobrews should have a beer as good as this one. Very pale and hazy yellow with a good yet collapsing white head. Very characterist aroma, with notes of citrus and coriander. Flavour is very refreshing, fruity and yeasty and with some bitterness in the end. Perfect balance between the sour notes from the wheat and the sweetness from the fruits. This one is a must!
Cask - handpumped - at the Cockney pub in Aarhus, Denmark. Golden colour with a small mostly diminishing white head. Aroma and taste of fruits, malts and hops.
Light hoppy nose, but weak. Pee yellow, flat carbonation, little fizzy layer of a head. Soapy and light watery aftertaste.
Dark amber color with fine head. Light sweet caramel malty taste, but a bit watery for me and not so christmas like.

Bottled. This is not a beer. It smells like a beer with hobs but the taste is like lemonade. I liked it anyway, because at the time I needed something cool and refreshing to drink. In denmark we call this a "lskedrik" :-) A nice alternative to beer.
Draught beer. High carb gold. Nose is lacking, mild apple. Mild flowery hops, with a touch of caramel.
I thougth I drank a blended banana, when I tasted this beer :-) No, its a good ordinary weissbier. Tastes a bit like the german Paulaner weissbier. Just not my favorite beer.
Nice dark yellow color and surprisingly flavorful for a pilsner. Really nice taste and feel. Try it!

Deep brown with long lasting malty head. Toasted, roasted malts and sweet malty sugar. The hops are a small part of the flavour, but there is a butterscotch chewey taste in a beautifully balanced beer, definitely better that the bottled version. A nice stout.

Quality lager appearance with a fresh lightly hopped aroma. The flavour slightly bitter but the dry finish is refreshing none the less when served ice cold. An above average European lager an my absolute favorite on a dry summer day!
Very good brown ale. You could drink a six-pack or you could just enjoy one with a good burger :-) Very drinkable for almost anyone. One of my favorite everyday beer!

Clear golden body with low but lasting white head that leaves some lace as it recedes. Lavender and floral hops with moderate bitterness over the soft, grainy, biscuity, toasty malt base with some honey tones. Medium body with fairly lively effervescence. A truly great beer!!
